WEBVTT

00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:06.240
In the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, amen.

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:13.640
The reading from the Sinaxadion for April 24, on which we commemorate, our righteous

00:00:13.640 --> 00:00:18.730
mother, Elizabeth, the Wonderworker.

00:00:18.730 --> 00:00:26.450
On the 24th of the month, we celebrate the memory of our Holy Mother, Elizabeth, the Wonderworker.

00:00:26.450 --> 00:00:31.410
Saint Elizabeth was given by God to her noble parents, devout Christians of Heraklia

00:00:31.410 --> 00:00:36.850
and Thrace, following a miraculous intervention by the Holy Marjorie Glicaria.

00:00:36.850 --> 00:00:42.210
From her earliest years, she learned the lives of the saints by heart, so that she was

00:00:42.210 --> 00:00:48.010
able to follow the model of their evangelical conduct in every circumstance.

00:00:48.010 --> 00:00:53.930
When she became an orphan, at the age of 12, she gave her inheritance away to the needy,

00:00:53.930 --> 00:01:00.690
freed her slaves, and entered the Convent of St. George, popularly referred to, as, of

00:01:00.690 --> 00:01:07.210
the Little Hill, in Constantinople, which was governed by her paternal aunt.

00:01:07.210 --> 00:01:12.770
Embracing with zeal all the labors of the ascetic life, she rapidly became a chosen vessel of

00:01:12.770 --> 00:01:14.450
divine grace.

00:01:14.450 --> 00:01:20.890
The eyes of her heart were unceasingly fixed on the divine beauty, and to that end, for three

00:01:20.890 --> 00:01:28.610
whole years she kept her gaze turned towards the ground, not allowing it to stray elsewhere.

00:01:28.610 --> 00:01:35.010
She wore a single tunic and walked around with bare feet, even in winter, but the love

00:01:35.010 --> 00:01:40.090
of God which burned in her heart served her for cloak and covering.

00:01:40.090 --> 00:01:47.170
The tears she shed during the recitation of the Psalms were sweeter than any bath or perfume,

00:01:47.170 --> 00:01:52.570
and for food she most often contented herself with the heavenly bread alone.

00:01:52.570 --> 00:01:57.970
When the Abyss was on the point of leaving this life, she named Elizabeth her successor, and

00:01:58.050 --> 00:02:06.010
it was the Holy Patriarch Yanadios in the years 458-471, who invested her.

00:02:06.010 --> 00:02:11.410
God then redoubled the effects of his grace, and the saint worked many miracles, healing

00:02:11.410 --> 00:02:17.210
incurable sicknesses, casting out demons, and predicting the future.

00:02:17.210 --> 00:02:23.290
She warned the Emperor Leo in advance of the terrible fire that was to ravage the capital

00:02:23.370 --> 00:02:29.970
in the year 465, which was also predicted by St. Daniel the Stylite, and it was thanks to

00:02:29.970 --> 00:02:35.970
these two saints that the city was preserved from complete destruction.

00:02:35.970 --> 00:02:41.450
As a sign of his gratitude, the Emperor gave her monastery the estate of St. Bobby-Las in

00:02:41.450 --> 00:02:43.290
the Hebdumon district.

00:02:43.290 --> 00:02:49.410
The place was, however, inhabited by a fearful dragon, which terrorized its inhabitants.

00:02:49.410 --> 00:02:55.970
The saint went to the place, taking with her the precious cross, and she killed the dragon,

00:02:55.970 --> 00:02:58.570
and trampled it under foot.

00:02:58.570 --> 00:03:05.450
Her reputation as a wonder-worker spread throughout the imperial city, and, like a new unmercinary,

00:03:05.450 --> 00:03:08.970
she healed the sicknesses of all who approached her.

00:03:08.970 --> 00:03:15.690
One day, during the divine liturgy, she went into ecstasy and saw the Holy Spirit descend

00:03:15.810 --> 00:03:20.810
like a great white luminous cloth to encompass the altar.

00:03:20.810 --> 00:03:26.410
Towards the end of her life, St. Elizabeth returned to Heraclia, her homeland, to venerate

00:03:26.410 --> 00:03:28.730
the holy places there.

00:03:28.730 --> 00:03:33.810
St. Gliccharia appeared to her, reminding her of the protection she had given her from her

00:03:33.810 --> 00:03:42.090
childhood, and inviting her to the heavenly country on the day after the feast of St. George.

00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:48.130
According to her monastery, Elizabeth gave her last instructions to the sisters, and,

00:03:48.130 --> 00:03:53.810
on the appointed day, having communicated in the holy mysteries, her face radiant like

00:03:53.810 --> 00:04:01.810
the sun, she stretched out her hands towards heaven, and gave her soul into God's hands.

00:04:01.810 --> 00:04:08.890
After having pronounced the words of righteous Simeon, Lord, now let us thou thy servant depart

00:04:08.890 --> 00:04:14.810
in peace, for my eyes have seen thy salvation.

00:04:14.810 --> 00:04:23.050
Elizabeth's body remained in corrupt, and was a source of healing for many centuries.

00:04:23.050 --> 00:04:30.410
Through the prayers of our Holy Father's, O Lord, Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us,

00:04:30.410 --> 00:04:31.410
and save us.
